    },
    {
      "id": "eb1bd2463b53328434c1ab90459de807fa7e5fb4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 793,
        "name": "Aurelien Degremont",
        "email": "adegremont@nvidia.com",
        "username": "degremoa"
      },
      "date": "2024-04-25 09:54:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI don't to delay that patch, so that could be a follow up, but:\n- why not autodetect the right path using pkg-config, as you shown in the LU ticket?\n- debian package systems can manage that for you automatically, if the service is in the debian/ dir (we could copy it there before building the deb packages). See that link for the way to handle service with different names: https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/306234/is-it-possible-to-install-two-services-for-one-package-using-dh-installinit-how",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "604914f958bbc2f79e029a15c7cd1fbac9067df9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2024-04-25 11:26:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified+1\n\nPassed enforced test review-dne-part-1 on RHEL 9.3/x86_64, Ubuntu 22.04/x86_64 uploaded by Trevis Autotest 2 from trevis-37vm1: https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/c22cc1a5-c1cb-4444-864f-70c3c0c2206b ran 4 tests.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "65aa31d8455a298db7d68a19c26821e640b873c1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 377,
        "name": "wc-checkpatch",
        "username": "hpdd-checkpatch",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2024-04-25 21:27:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nLooks good to me.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "259b86c9b594fec57fbff08144cf8a461dbab953",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2024-04-25 23:54:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> I don't to delay that patch, so that could be a follow up, but:\n> - why not autodetect the right path using pkg-config, as you shown in the LU ticket?\n> - debian package systems can manage that for you automatically, if the service is in the debian/ dir (we could copy it there before building the deb packages). See that link for the way to handle service with different names: https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/306234/is-it-possible-to-install-two-services-for-one-package-using-dh-installinit-how\n\nThank you for the comments, Aurelien.\nBy default, the right path is autodetected by pkg-config in lustre/autoconf/lustre-core.m4 while running configure command. This patch doesn't change that. It resolves the issue of specified \"--with-systemdsystemunitdir\" option not passing to the configure command in \"make debs\".\nIn addition, \"lib/systemd/system\" is hardcoded in debian/lustre-{client,server}-utils.install.in, which is incorrect on Ubuntu 24.04 and causes \"dh_install -p lustre-client-utils\" fail to find the path. So, this patch updates that path with the correct value specified by \"--with-systemdsystemunitdir\" option, the value of which is autodetected by pkg-config.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b5f75114e78275faf40c113c112bfb41399cc09d",
      "author": {
